## What NOT to Do

These are the most common mistakes. Avoid them.

| Never | Instead |
|-------|---------|
| Access the database directly from Next.js | Call the Symfony API |
| Duplicate business logic in the frontend | The API validates and enforces rules |
| Skip updating `shared-types` when changing a response | Update types first, then code |
| Commit `.env.local` or `.env` | They are gitignored; use `.env.example` as the template |
| Use `localStorage` for auth tokens | Use httpOnly cookies set by Next.js API routes |
| Write logic in a Symfony Controller | Write it in a Service{% if use_ddd %} or Domain class{% endif %} |
| Edit a Doctrine migration after it has been applied | Create a new migration |
| Use `any` in TypeScript | Find or create the right type |
| Install a new major dependency without an ADR | Write the ADR first, then install |
| Return different JSON shapes from similar endpoints | Follow the contract in `docs/api-contract.md` |
| Merge a PR with failing tests | Fix the tests first |

